{"body": "Well, to fix the code during our rails migration (which still isn't complete after 3 months -- 75k LOC app), that's exactly what I had to do.\r\n\r\nRails 2.3 version\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n:key => request.xhr?\r\n```\r\n\r\nRails 3.1 version:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\n:key => !!request.xhr?\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy two arguments, , were:\r\n\r\n- This needlessly broke API compatibility between 2.3 and 3.1\r\n- Using `!!some_method?` is bad style, I understand using `!!some_method` but the `?` should indicate a boolean return value.\r\n\r\nThe second argument might be nitpicky (and I suppose just my opinion), but the first isn't.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4667453", "created_at": "2012-03-23T20:37:47Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5329#issuecomment-4667453", "updated_at": "2012-03-23T20:38:15Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5329, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/clifton", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc27181a18d3b30d14d66a1a56c068548.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "clifton", "type": "User", "id": 14217, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523819bdbd3543c15100e1fc"}, "id": 4667453, "issue_url": "https://api.gith